I'm not sure but I'd double check the "initialization code" is stored somewhere that the SPC file doesn't use, and maybe you should be carefully when initialisating $f0 - $ff values - they are registers and it may be bad if you simply "copy" the values as it from the .spc file. You'd only want to copy the values at $f0, $f1, $f8, $f9 and $fa.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Wed Dec 16, 2009 1:35 am</p><hr />
